  "texts": [
    "We ask the vendor to annotate a detailed rubric-based evaluation of the generated response to each user prompt given the proposed rubric.",
    "Specifically, annotators need to go through every rubric and decide whether it is met or not, and provide justification (i.e., chain-of-thought for the judge) for their judgment.",
    "This golden set of evaluations, referred to as D golden, is used to develop the rubric verifier for RL training with the following two stages.",
    "We conduct supervised finetuning (SFT) to cold-start the model to evaluate responses based on rubrics like expert human raters.",
    "We form a portion of D golden as the SFT dataset D SFT = {(x j, y j)} n j=1, where x j is the rubric verifier prompt including the user prompt, rubric, and model-generated response, and y j is the human-annotated rubric-based evaluation."
